The article discusses the passage of the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act, which is the first significant piece of gun safety legislation in nearly 30 years. The author emphasizes the need to keep dangerous firearms out of dangerous hands, especially considering that guns are the leading cause of death for children in America. The article highlights the passing of an assault weapons ban by House Democrats, which aims to keep weapons of war off the streets and reduce crime. The author calls for the Senate to quickly pass the bill, stating that ensuring the safety of families, children, homes, communities, and the nation is of utmost importance.